  "title": "Assistant Engineer/ Engineer, Instrumentation",
  "description": "<p><strong>Duties &amp; Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p>· Manage equipment to monitor instrumentation systems</p>\n<p>· Responsible for instrumentation installation and network establishment</p>\n<p>· Monitor work progress and preparation of necessary reports</p>\n<p>· Liaise and coordinate with contractors, clients and co-workers to ensure smooth completion</p>\n<p>· To troubleshoot, repair and resolve technical issues pertaining to electrical/ network</p>\n<p>· Attend meetings when required</p>\n<p>· Any other duties as assigned</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p>· Degree/ Diploma in Civil Engineering or equivalent</p>\n<p>· Min. 1 year of experience</p>\n<p>· IT/ Software background is an advantageous</p>\n<p>· Keen interest in geotechnical instrumentation and relevant experience will be advantageous</p>\n<p>· Able to work independently and as a team</p>\n<p>· Good communication and interpersonal skills</p>",
